an><hr size=1> Np, Kia.<br><br>What blows me away is how little they make.  $15,000-$20,000 is not much for the cost of living in Tokyo or most of Japan.  It's always been my dream to go over there to learn to draw and get a job (not to mention just learning Japanese), but for that kinda salary...uh...it's doesn't sound too practical.  <br><br>It seems like animated movies here in America come down to just making a profit.  Maybe that's why so little is made.  In Japan it's more about quantity.  I'm not saying the stuff they do make is not good, just that they don't need every movie to be a blockbuster.  <br><br>I guess the best quote from the article is: <br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The Japanese culture has made a very important observation: Animation isn't only for kids.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Too bad the rest of the world doesn't really think like that.  Anime is a very good way to tell a story.  I bet a bunch of Hollywood bombs could be remade as an animated movie and be blockbusters.   <p><MARQUEE BEHAVIOR=SLIDE DIRECTION=LEFT SCROLLAMOUNT=100 ><b>Kwiix ·R·</b></MARQUEE> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urocketpig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rocketpig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/15/02 9:36:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9664.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rocketpig.net/images/Click-Icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: R</span><hr size=1> Wow, that's a pretty informative little article... I just wish it was a little longer, I would like to hear some more of the details instead of a general overview.<br><br>I didn't know animators were that underpaid. <p>No one has e